node.title: NT records one new COVID case in outbreak, three presumptive cases detected in remote communities
node.description: The Northern Territory has recorded one new case of COVID-19 related to the current outbreak, but authorities say three presumptive cases have been detected in remote communities.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded one new case of COVID-19 related to the current outbreak, but authorities say three presumptive cases have been detected in remote communities.", "Of the three presumptive cases, two are in Timber Creek and one is in Kalkarindji.", "The new confirmed case is a close contact of another case that tested positive in Howard Springs.", "The new case brings the total cases related to the current outbreak to 88.", "But NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles said authorities expect that number to rise to 91 as they await confirmation of the three presumptive cases.", "There has also been one positive case from an international repatriation flight that arrived in the NT from Johannesburg.", "More to come."]
